{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "buddhism-expert",
    "senderColor": "red",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Buddhism expert: No, keep First/Second/Zeroth numbering",
    "content": "**No. Keep First/Second/Zeroth. The renaming creates serious problems.**\n\n**The core issue: \"Ultimate Reality\" is the most heavily claimed term in Buddhist-Western comparative philosophy.** In Buddhist English, \"Ultimate Reality\" is the standard rendering of *paramartha-satya* (勝義諦) or *paramartha* (真実/勝義). The author's 第一実在 is explicitly NOT paramartha -- it is phenomena as encountered, the starting point, the indubitable ground. Calling phenomena \"Ultimate Reality\" would make every Buddhist-literate reader (and many general philosophy readers) think the author is making a claim about what is *most real in the ontological hierarchy*. The author's footnote 25 explicitly denies this: \"第一実在 is a name, not an ontological claim.\"\n\nThe whole point of the numbering is that it is *structural-sequential* (what we encounter first, what we build second, what we posit as zeroth), not *hierarchical* (what is most real). \"Ultimate\" destroys this by reintroducing hierarchy.\n\n**\"Secondary\" is also wrong.** It implies derivativeness and lesser status. But the author's 第二実在 includes the entire objective world as we understand it, all of science, all of metaphysics. Calling this \"secondary\" makes it sound like an afterthought. The author's point is that it is *second in the order of construction* (built upon phenomena), not second in importance.\n\n**The numbering system is itself philosophically significant.** The author chose ordinal numbers deliberately: they encode the *order of epistemic access*, not a ranking of reality. First = what we encounter first. Second = what we construct second. Zeroth = what we posit as logically prior but cannot access. This is clean, neutral, and does not smuggle in value judgments. Any move to qualitative names (\"Ultimate,\" \"Secondary\") corrupts this neutrality.\n\nKeep First Reality, Second Reality, Zeroth Reality. They are clear, faithful, and do not activate unwanted philosophical associations.\n"
  }
}
